headlines.description: — LaMelo Ball had a good first three quarters in Brooklyn, then decided it was best if he watched the fourth.
headlines.shortLinkText: Hornets pull away, beat Nets 111-95 for first 3-0 start

events.name: Orlando Magic at New York Knicks

headlines.description: — Terrence Ross scored all 22 of his points in the fourth quarter, and the Orlando Magic beat the New York Knicks 110-104 on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Ross' 22-point 4th quarter leads Magic over Knicks 110-104

headlines.description: — Jayson Tatum had 31 points and nine rebounds and the Boston Celtics avoided their first 0-3 start since the 2013-14 season with a 107-97 win over the Houston Rockets on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Tatum scores 31, Celtics get first win, 107-97 over Houston

headlines.description: — Seth Curry's start resembled some of his big brother's hottest streaks.
headlines.shortLinkText: Curry scores 28 points to help 76ers top Thunder, 115-103

events.name: Golden State Warriors at Sacramento Kings

headlines.description: — Stephen Curry scored 27 points and became the first player in Warriors franchise history to reach 5,000 assists, helping Golden State improve to 3-0 with a 119-107 victory over the Sacramento Kings on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Stephen Curry reaches 5,000 assists, Warriors beat Kings

events.name: Memphis Grizzlies at Los Angeles Lakers

headlines.description: — Carmelo Anthony got the game ball after the Los Angeles Lakers’ first victory of the season.
